8 third-party investment management firm, (ii) the staff of the State Treasurer overseeing the Fund,
9 and (iii) the third-party investment management firm's employees selecting or overseeing Fund
10 investments do not provide services for compensation (as an employee, consultant, or otherwise),
11 within two years after the end of their service to the Fund, to any entity in which an investment
12 from the Fund was made.
13 (b1) Conflict of Interest Policy. – The Investment Authority shall adopt a policy to prevent
14 conflicts of interest. This policy shall include a provision prohibiting all of the following
15 individuals from providing services for compensation to any entity in which an investment from
16 the Venture Capital Multiplier Fund was made within two years after the end of that individual's
17 service to the Fund:
18 (1) The designee of the State Treasurer and Governor who selected the third-party
19 investment management firm prior to the creation of the Investment Authority.
20 (2) The designee of the Investment Authority who selected the third-party
21 investment management firm.
22 (3) The staff of the Department of State Treasurer or of the Investment Authority
23 overseeing the Fund.
24 (4) The third-party investment management firm's employees selecting or
25 overseeing Fund investments.
